  • Method Details

    • addCommand

      public boolean addCommand​(Command command, java.lang.String commandName)
      Add a command to this CommandManager, which means this command manager can execute it.
      Parameters:
      command - The command to add.
      commandName - The name the command will be known by. Uses this alias instead of the name in the Command obj.
      Returns:
      True if the command was added, false if there is already a command by this name and it was not added.

    • addCommand

      public boolean addCommand​(Command command)
      Add a command to this CommandManager, which means this command manager can execute it. This differs from the overload that takes in a command name in that it uses the name the Command object contains.
      Parameters:
      command - The command to add.
      Returns:
      True if the command was added, false if there is already a command by this name and it was not added.

    • processCommands

      public void processCommands()
      Takes in messages from the command queue, constructs them into a Command object. It then places them on the internal command queue for later execution.

    • doCommands

      public void doCommands()
      Loops through all the commands in the queue and executes them.
